        "subject": "LU-10279 tests: Reduce chance of writeback in 101",
        "message": "LU-10279 tests: Reduce chance of writeback in 101\n\nDespite disabling the time based dirty writeback in the\nsanityn 101 tests, analysis of test failures shows that\noccasionally some non-Lustre process is flushing our dirty\ndata.\n\nA possible culprit is memory pressure.  Drop caches and\nlocks before each of these tests to reduce the chance of\nwriteback.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial testlist=sanityn\nTest-Parameters: fstype=ldiskfs mdscount=2 mdtcount=4 testlist=sanityn,sanityn\nTest-Parameters: fstype=zfs mdscount=2 mdtcount=4 testlist=sanityn,sanityn\n\nSigned-off-by: Patrick Farrell <pfarrell@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I5ddbe88f82a8255fe808155756cdadc4cd08b891\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
